CatDescriptText: Elizabeth (Libby) Goins, beauty shop owner, 2115 Centre Avenue, was part of the Pittsburgher's Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 5, 1959 with question: "Do you believe Allegheny County Democrats and Republicans have selected their best candidates for public offices in past 10 years?" Answer reads: "No, I don't believe they have.  I believe the Democrats could have done better in the choice of their present governor."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth "Libby" Goins wearing light colored short sleeved dress, posed in front of the Beauty Box, 2115 Centre Avenue, Hill District
